247
00:11:33,759 --> 00:11:35,894
- WHAT DID YOU SAY
  YOUR NAME WAS ?
- KATIE.

248
00:11:35,894 --> 00:11:38,463
- I'D LOVE A CUP OF JOE.
- SURE.

249
00:11:38,463 --> 00:11:40,933
UH, COFFEE ALL AROUND ?
MA'AM ?

250
00:11:40,933 --> 00:11:42,935
NOTHING, THANKS.

251
00:11:40,933 --> 00:11:42,935
WE'RE GONNA
BE HERE A SPELL.

252
00:11:42,935 --> 00:11:45,470
THERE'S A LOT
OF WHITE STUFF BETWEEN HERE
AND AIR FORCE ONE.

253
00:11:45,471 --> 00:11:47,339
GOOD THING I GOT
MY CAMPAIGNING IN.

254
00:11:45,471 --> 00:11:47,339
ABSOLUTELY.

255
00:11:47,339 --> 00:11:51,276
- I DIDN'T VOTE.
- KATIE.  COULD HAVE
  USED YOU OUT THERE TODAY.

256
00:11:51,276 --> 00:11:53,745
[ Chuckles ]
I'M SURE YOU DID FINE.

257
00:11:53,745 --> 00:11:55,948
THAT'S WHAT
THEY'RE TELLING ME,
BUT PERHAPS YOUR VOTE...

258
00:11:55,948 --> 00:11:58,149
COULD HAVE TAKEN ME
FROM VICTORY TO MANDATE.

259
00:11:58,149 --> 00:12:00,018
HE LOOKS A LOT OLDER
THAN ON TV.

260
00:12:00,018 --> 00:12:02,855
[ Emerson ]
OKAY.  LOOKING FORWARD
TO THAT CHILIBURGER.

261
00:12:02,855 --> 00:12:05,423
DON'T SAY ANYTHING STUPID,
OKAY ?

262
00:12:02,855 --> 00:12:05,423
YOU'RE TELLING ME THAT ?

263
00:12:05,423 --> 00:12:07,425
HE'S COMING OVER.

264
00:12:05,423 --> 00:12:07,425
HOW DO I LOOK ?

265
00:12:07,425 --> 00:12:09,829
HI THERE.
WALT EMERSON.

266
00:12:07,425 --> 00:12:09,829
HI.

267
00:12:09,829 --> 00:12:12,930
HI, I'M, UM,
LIZZIE WOODS.

268
00:12:09,829 --> 00:12:12,930
PLEASURE.

269
00:12:12,931 --> 00:12:15,000
NICE TO MEET YOU.
WALT EMERSON.  HI.

270
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,235
TAYLOR WOODS.
IT'S AN HONOR, SIR.

271
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,235
TAYLOR.

272
00:12:17,235 --> 00:12:20,806
YOU'VE GOT
THAT NEW YORK SENSE
ABOUT YOU, NO ?

273
00:12:20,806 --> 00:12:22,941
VERY GOOD, SIR.
GOLDMAN SACHS.

274
00:12:22,941 --> 00:12:24,843
I'M THE OIL AND
MINERAL ANALYST.

275
00:12:24,843 --> 00:12:27,378
OF COURSE YOU ARE.
WHOSE MOVE IS IT ?

276
00:12:27,379 --> 00:12:29,681
UH, THAT WOULD BE
MY MOVE.

277
00:12:27,379 --> 00:12:29,681
MAY I ?

278
00:12:29,681 --> 00:12:32,151
OH, YES, YES.

279
00:12:29,681 --> 00:12:32,151
HAVE A LOOK HERE.

280
00:12:33,718 --> 00:12:36,889
UH-HUH.
WELL, WELL, WELL.

281
00:12:39,591 --> 00:12:43,662
WOW.  IS THIS, UH,
KASPAROV DEEP BLUE,
GAME THREE ?

282
00:12:45,430 --> 00:12:48,500
I-- I DON'T
THINK SO, SIR.

283
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:52,438
[ Chuckling ]

284
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:52,438
NO, I'D SAY SHE'S
ABOUT SEVEN MOVES AWAY.

285
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:54,340
HMM.

286
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:54,340
REALLY.

287
00:12:54,340 --> 00:12:56,475
SO, YOU TWO, UH,

288
00:12:56,475 --> 00:12:58,410
SATISFIED AMERICANS,
WOULD YOU SAY ?

289
00:12:58,410 --> 00:13:02,381
- ABSOLUTELY, MR. PRESIDENT.
  WE'VE BEEN SO HAPPY THIS YEAR.
- MY ONLY--

290
00:13:02,381 --> 00:13:05,184
MY ONLY PROBLEM--
EXCUSE ME, I JUST
WANT TO GET THIS--

291
00:13:05,184 --> 00:13:07,819
I JU--
I JUST WANT TO GET
SOMETHING IN HERE.

292
00:13:07,820 --> 00:13:10,889
MY ONLY DEBATE
WITH YOU IS THE
SOCIAL SECURITY ISSUE.

293
00:13:10,889 --> 00:13:13,258
IS THAT RIGHT.

294
00:13:10,889 --> 00:13:13,258
I THINK YOUR MOVING
THE AGE TO 73...

295
00:13:13,258 --> 00:13:17,896
FOR BENEFITS
ON PENSION FUNDS
AND STOCK PORTFOLIOS...

296
00:13:17,896 --> 00:13:20,098
IS JUST GONNA TRIGGER
PANIC SELLING.

297
00:13:20,098 --> 00:13:24,536
ANY IDEA HOW WE CAME ABOUT THE
AGE OF 65 FOR SOCIAL SECURITY ?

298
00:13:20,098 --> 00:13:24,536
NO.

299
00:13:24,536 --> 00:13:28,372
ACTUALLY, UH, NO,
COME TO THINK OF IT.

300
00:13:28,373 --> 00:13:32,210
I MEAN, WHY NOT
70 OR 80 OR 64 ?

301
00:13:32,210 --> 00:13:35,281
I HAVE NO IDEA.

302
00:13:32,210 --> 00:13:35,281
WE ADOPTED
THE SOCIAL SECURITY SYSTEM...

303
00:13:35,281 --> 00:13:37,983
[ Cameraman ]  RELOADING.

304
00:13:35,281 --> 00:13:37,983
FROM BISMARCK,
HOOK, LINE AND SINKER.

305
00:13:37,983 --> 00:13:41,386
BISMARCK WAS AN S.O.B.
JUST LOOKING TO BOOST
HIS POPULARITY...

306
00:13:41,386 --> 00:13:43,222
WITH HIS SOCIAL
WELFARE SYSTEM.

307
00:13:43,222 --> 00:13:46,124
SO HE GOES TO HIS ACTUARIES,
AND THEY ASSURE HIM--

308
00:13:46,124 --> 00:13:47,960
THIS IS
THE LATE 1800s.

309
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:51,897
SO THEY TELL HIM
THAT EVERYONE'S GONNA BE DEAD
BY THE AGE OF 65.

310
00:13:51,897 --> 00:13:54,533
- OF COURSE,
  TODAY IT'S EQUIVALENT TO 105.
- UNBELIEVABLE.

311
00:13:54,533 --> 00:13:57,069
FASCINATING.

312
00:13:54,533 --> 00:13:57,069
IT'S 9:00,
MR. PRESIDENT.

313
00:13:57,069 --> 00:14:01,473
OKAY.  SO THAT'S HOW
WE'RE STARTING TO THINK
IN TERMS OF 73.

314
00:14:01,473 --> 00:14:05,077
I HOPE
I DIDN'T INTERRUPT THE GAME.
I SHOULD GO CHECK THE RESULTS.

315
00:14:05,077 --> 00:14:07,079
NICE MEETING YOU BOTH.

316
00:14:05,077 --> 00:14:07,079
THANK YOU.

317
00:14:05,077 --> 00:14:07,079
EDIFYING.

318
00:14:07,079 --> 00:14:09,414
THANK YOU
FOR THE TIP.

319
00:14:07,079 --> 00:14:09,414
GOOD LUCK TO YOU.

320
00:14:09,414 --> 00:14:11,282
OOP.
I'M SORRY.

321
00:14:09,414 --> 00:14:11,282
GOT IT.

322
00:14:11,282 --> 00:14:13,351
YOU'RE GONNA NEED
THAT ONE, HUH ?

323
00:14:11,282 --> 00:14:13,351
THAT'S OKAY.

324
00:14:13,351 --> 00:14:15,320
GOOD LUCK.

325
00:14:13,351 --> 00:14:15,320
GOOD LUCK
TO YOU.

326
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:18,924
YOU HAVE OUR VOTE.
[ Exhaling ]

327
00:14:18,924 --> 00:14:21,060
KASPAROV
DEEP BLUE.

328
00:14:18,924 --> 00:14:21,060
HE'S VERY SHORT.

329
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:23,529
WHAT DO YOU TWO
HAVE IN THE POOL ?

330
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:23,529
FIFTY-EIGHT.

331
00:14:24,863 --> 00:14:26,431
FIFTY-NINE.

332
00:14:24,863 --> 00:14:26,431
THE POLLS IN COLORADO
HAVE NOW CLOSED.

333
00:14:26,431 --> 00:14:29,568
SIXTY-ONE.

334
00:14:26,431 --> 00:14:29,568
HERE AT IBS, WE ARE READY
TO PROJECT A WINNER...

335
00:14:29,568 --> 00:14:31,436
IN THE COLORADO PRIMARY.

336
00:14:31,436 --> 00:14:34,139
WITH ALL PRECINCTS
HAVING REPORTED,
IBS IS PROJECTING...

337
00:14:34,139 --> 00:14:36,441
THAT PRESIDENT WALTER EMERSON...

338
00:14:34,139 --> 00:14:36,441
<i> AND... YES !</i>

339
00:14:36,441 --> 00:14:40,178
THERE IT IS.
CASPER THE FUCKING GHOST.

340
00:14:36,441 --> 00:14:40,178
WILL WIN THE PRIMARY WITH 63%--

341
00:14:40,178 --> 00:14:42,447
WE GOT THE PRICK
BY THE BALLS.
HERE'S WHAT WE DO.

342
00:14:42,447 --> 00:14:45,417
CALL HIM UP AND TELL HIM
THE DEAL'S STILL ON, BUT HE
HAS WITHDRAW BY NOON TOMORROW.

343
00:14:45,417 --> 00:14:49,388
OTHERWISE, NO DEAL.
HE'S GOT NO MANEUVERING ROOM
TO EVEN CHANGE THE PLATFORM.

344
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:52,123
SO, WE MAKE HIM FEEL
LIKE HE'S GOT A LITTLE
WRIGGLE ROOM, RIGHT ?

345
00:14:52,123 --> 00:14:54,492
CUT HIM OFF AT THE KNEES,
MAKE HIM THINK HE CAN WALK.

346
00:14:54,492 --> 00:14:57,295
WHY DON'T WE
JUST PROCEED AHEAD ?
WE'RE GONNA WIN ANYWAYS.

347
00:14:57,295 --> 00:15:00,232
LET'S JUST--

348
00:14:57,295 --> 00:15:00,232
NO, HE'S AT THE HYATT.
I'M GONNA CALL HIM NOW.

349
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:03,935
IF HE'S COZY IN THAT
HOTEL ROOM WITH A BLONDE,

350
00:15:03,935 --> 00:15:06,537
HE'S A LOT WISER
THAN I.

351
00:15:06,538 --> 00:15:08,940
WHEN DO YOU THINK
WE'RE GONNA GET OUT
OF HERE, BY THE WAY ?

352
00:15:08,940 --> 00:15:13,278
TRACEY'S GOT A BALLET RECITAL
TOMORROW, AND ALEXANDRA'S GOT
MY BLOOD OATH ON THIS ONE.

353
00:15:13,278 --> 00:15:16,481
WELL, UH, AIR FORCE ONE
IS ABOUT 20 MINUTES FROM HERE
AT PETERSON AIR FORCE BASE,

354
00:15:16,481 --> 00:15:19,551
AND AS SOON AS
THE WEATHER GETS BETTER--
IT CLEARS UP, IT'S SAFE--

355
00:15:19,551 --> 00:15:23,121
WE GET MARINE ONE TO COME,
GET US OUT OF HERE--
23-SKIDDOO, WE'RE ALL SET.

356
00:15:23,121 --> 00:15:26,057
OKAY.  WELL,
LET'S JUST DO
WHAT WE NEED TO DO.

357
00:15:26,057 --> 00:15:29,495
WHAT IF CASPER
WANTS TO TALK TO YOU ?

358
00:15:29,495 --> 00:15:31,297
WELL, I'LL--
I GUESS I'LL--

359
00:15:31,297 --> 00:15:33,999
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
YOU DON'T WANT
TO TALK TO HIM.

360
00:15:33,999 --> 00:15:36,435
YOU'RE TALKING
TO YOUR CONSTITUENTS.

361
00:15:36,435 --> 00:15:40,238
MAYBE WE SHOULDN'T BE
SURPRISED THAT HE RECEIVED
THE VOTES THAT HE DID.

362
00:15:40,239 --> 00:15:43,875
MANY PEOPLE VIEW EMERSON
AS NOT PRESIDENTIAL.

363
00:15:43,875 --> 00:15:46,878
HE'S VERY VICE PRESIDENTIAL,
VERY SECOND BANANA.

364
00:15:46,878 --> 00:15:49,381
HIS EXPERIENCE IN FOREIGN POSTS
HAS CERTAINLY BEEN STRONG.

365
00:15:49,381 --> 00:15:52,083
HE BOASTS PROBABLY
ONE OF THE BEST RESUMES
SINCE GEORGE BUSH.

366
00:15:52,083 --> 00:15:55,153
TRUE, BUT HE DOESN'T HAVE
THE PHYSICAL BEARING
OF A PRESIDENT.

367
00:15:55,153 --> 00:15:59,758
TRAITS THAT WELL COULD HAVE
BEEN ASCRIBED TO HAR--
HOLD ON ONE MOMENT.

368
00:15:59,758 --> 00:16:02,094
OKAY, THIS ISN'T--
I'LL SAY THIS QUICK.

369
00:16:02,094 --> 00:16:05,997
THINK ABOUT IT.
WE'LL ALL BE HAPPY
IN AUGUST, OKAY ?  HUH ?

370
00:16:05,997 --> 00:16:09,168
[ Irving On TV ]  APPARENTLY
THIS IS A MASSIVE MILITARY
ACTION FROM THE MIDDLE EAST.

371
00:16:09,168 --> 00:16:12,404
OUR FIRST INDICATIONS ARE...

372
00:16:09,168 --> 00:16:12,404
NO, I SAID IF YOU--
WE'LL ALL BE--

373
00:16:12,404 --> 00:16:15,173
THAT THERE IS
A LARGE TROOP MOVEMENT
IN THE GULF AREA.

374
00:16:15,173 --> 00:16:17,943
OKAY.  APPARENTLY ISRAELI RADIO
HAS JUST ISSUED...

375
00:16:15,173 --> 00:16:17,943
GOOD NEWS OR BAD NEWS ?

376
00:16:17,943 --> 00:16:20,179
A NATIONWIDE CALL-UP
FOR THEIR RESERVES.

377
00:16:20,179 --> 00:16:22,514
THAT'S IN RESPONSE
TO WHAT APPEARED TO BE...

378
00:16:22,514 --> 00:16:25,217
SIR, YOU SHOULD CHECK THIS OUT.

379
00:16:22,514 --> 00:16:25,217
A LARGE-SCALE MANEUVER FROM
THE IRAQI ARMY AND AIR FORCE.

380
00:16:25,217 --> 00:16:27,686
WHAT IS IT ?

381
00:16:25,217 --> 00:16:27,686
<i> [ Marsh ]  WHAT'S
 THE STORY, HOWARD ?</i>

382
00:16:27,686 --> 00:16:29,888
WHAT'S HAPPENED ?

383
00:16:27,686 --> 00:16:29,888
NO INDICATION OF
AMERICAN TROOPS IN THE REGION...

384
00:16:29,888 --> 00:16:32,857
HAVING ENCOUNTERED
ANY HOSTILITIES.

385
00:16:29,888 --> 00:16:32,857
GAYLE ?

386
00:16:32,857 --> 00:16:35,194
OKAY.  BEAR WITH ME,
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN.

387
00:16:35,194 --> 00:16:37,829
THIS IS--  LET'S JUST
GET THIS TOGETHER.

388
00:16:37,829 --> 00:16:39,964
OKAY.  ALL RIGHT,
HERE WE GO.

389
00:16:39,965 --> 00:16:44,035
WE HAVE SOME INFORMATION
FROM AT LEAST TWO CORRESPONDENTS
IN THE MIDDLE EAST.

390
00:16:44,035 --> 00:16:49,641
THIS HAS NOT YET BEEN VERIFIED
BY ANY GOVERNMENT SOURCES,
AND WE SHOULD UNDERSCORE THAT.

391
00:16:49,641 --> 00:16:53,377
BUT--  OKAY.  OKAY,
WE ARE NOW GETTING WORD
FROM OUR CORRESPONDENTS...

392
00:16:53,378 --> 00:16:55,580
IN BAGHDAD AND KUWAIT.

393
00:16:55,580 --> 00:16:58,884
UDEI HUSSEIN,
THE DICTATOR OF IRAQ,

394
00:16:58,884 --> 00:17:01,352
HAS TAKEN A MILITARY FORCE
AND HAS CROSSED...

395
00:17:01,352 --> 00:17:05,290
HIS SOUTHEAST BORDER
INTO KUWAIT, HEADING DIRECTLY
FOR KUWAIT CITY.

396
00:17:05,290 --> 00:17:07,692
BOY'S GOT SOME BALLS.

397
00:17:05,290 --> 00:17:07,692
[ Irving On TV ]
OKAY.

398
00:17:07,692 --> 00:17:12,631
ALL RIGHT.  OUR INITIAL REPORTS
ARE THAT THE UNITED NATIONS-LED
AMERICAN PEACEKEEPING FORCE...

399
00:17:12,631 --> 00:17:14,633
HAS BEEN OVERRUN.

400
00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:16,534
HOWARD, GET SECDEF
ON THE LINE.

401
00:17:16,534 --> 00:17:19,604
WE'RE TRYING TO NAIL DOWN
THE SIGNIFICANT DETAILS.

402
00:17:19,604 --> 00:17:21,439
CAN-- CAN WE--
OKAY.

403
00:17:21,439 --> 00:17:23,542
<i> WE HAVE JOHN MARINO
 ON A CELL PHONE.</i>

404
00:17:21,439 --> 00:17:23,542
<i> HOW IS THIS HAPPENING ?</i>

405
00:17:23,541 --> 00:17:26,977
WHERE DID THIS COME FROM
ALL OF A SUDDEN ?

406
00:17:23,541 --> 00:17:26,977
I-I-I DON'T KNOW.

407
00:17:26,978 --> 00:17:29,480
<i> [ Irving ]
 JOHN, CAN YOU HEAR ME ?</i>

408
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:31,416
<i> JOHN ?</i>

409
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:31,416
<i> MARSH ?</i>

410
00:17:31,416 --> 00:17:33,918
- [ Irving ]  OKAY,
  WE'RE HAVING SOME PROBLEMS.
- [ Emerson ]  MARSHALL.

411
00:17:33,919 --> 00:17:35,954
IBS MILITARY ANALYSTS
WILL BE WITH US SHORTLY.

412
00:17:35,954 --> 00:17:37,922
SO FAR, NO CONTACT
FROM THE WHITE HOUSE,

413
00:17:37,922 --> 00:17:41,626
OTHER THAN A STATEMENT THAT
THE PRESIDENT IS MONITORING
THE SITUATION CAREFULLY...

414
00:17:41,626 --> 00:17:43,829
AND THAT HE IS
GRAVELY CONCERNED.

415
00:17:45,563 --> 00:17:47,566
<i> [ Emerson ]
 I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
 WHAT ABOUT OUR SATELLITES ?</i>

416
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:51,436
HOW COME WE DIDN'T--

417
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:51,436
THAT'S A QUESTION
FOR SECDEF, SIR.

418
00:17:51,436 --> 00:17:53,438
HE'S BEEN DISTRACTED
BY THE KOREAN MESS.

419
00:17:53,439 --> 00:17:56,008
YEAH, I SHOULD SAY,
WHEN A NATION CAN INVADE
ANOTHER NATION...

420
00:17:56,008 --> 00:17:57,842
AND OVERRUN
AMERICAN TROOPS.

421
00:17:57,842 --> 00:18:00,445
SIR, MAYBE WE DON'T KNOW
BECAUSE IT DID NOT HAPPEN.

422
00:17:57,842 --> 00:18:00,445
IT HAPPENED.

423
00:18:00,445 --> 00:18:02,347
IT'S ALL OVER THE NEWS

424
00:18:00,445 --> 00:18:02,347
WE DON'T HAVE
CONFIRMATION.

425
00:18:02,347 --> 00:18:05,250
WE HAVE TO ASSUME IT HAPPENED.

426
00:18:02,347 --> 00:18:05,250
DOESN'T THIS BASTARD
GET IT ?

427
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:06,851
I'D SAY NOT.

428
00:18:06,851 --> 00:18:10,055
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
WE HAD TROOPS IN KUWAIT.

429
00:18:06,851 --> 00:18:10,055
TECHNICALLY, WE DID NOT.

430
00:18:10,055 --> 00:18:12,057
THEY WERE UNDER
U.N. SUPERVISION.

431
00:18:12,057 --> 00:18:13,959
IT WAS OUR TURN
IN THE HELSINKI ROTATION.

432
00:18:13,959 --> 00:18:16,595
HOW MANY TROOPS WERE THERE ?

433
00:18:13,959 --> 00:18:16,595
THREE--  THREE-TWENTY.
I'M NOT SURE.

434
00:18:16,595 --> 00:18:19,163
YOU'RE NOT SURE ?
THERE'S A BIG DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN 300 AND 320.

435
00:18:19,163 --> 00:18:25,203
EITHER WAY, I'D RATHER HAVE
NO TROOPS THAN A SMALL FORCE
THAT ACTS AS AN INDUCEMENT.

436
00:18:25,203 --> 00:18:27,639
JESUS.

437
00:18:25,203 --> 00:18:27,639
[ Irving On TV ]
THE GIGANTIC ISRAELI RESERVES--

438
00:18:27,639 --> 00:18:31,341
WELL, DOES HUSSEIN THINK THAT
WE'RE JUST GONNA LET IT STAND ?

439
00:18:31,342 --> 00:18:33,345
[ Irving On TV ]
THE ISRAELIS HAVE BEGUN
A FULL MOBILIZATION.

440
00:18:33,345 --> 00:18:35,980
<i> [ Marsh ]
 I THINK HE DOES,
 THE LITTLE FUCK.</i>

441
00:18:35,980 --> 00:18:40,184
I DON'T NEED THAT, MARSH.
WE NEED TO MAKE THIS VERY,
VERY CLEAR FOR HIM.

442
00:18:40,184 --> 00:18:43,355
<i> WE WILL.  WHEN WE GET HOME,
 WE'LL SEND THE BASTARD HOME
 WITHOUT ANY SUPPER...</i>

443
00:18:43,355 --> 00:18:46,391
AND WE SLAP HIM
WITH EVERY ECONOMIC AND
DIPLOMATIC SANCTION THERE IS.

444
00:18:46,391 --> 00:18:48,894
SIR, I HAVE
SECRETARY HANCOCK ON THE LINE.

445
00:18:48,894 --> 00:18:51,663
WELL, WE'RE DOING SOMETHING.

446
00:18:48,894 --> 00:18:51,663
<i> [ Marsh ]
 YES, WE ARE.</i>

447
00:18:51,663 --> 00:18:53,966
<i> OKAY, LET'S
 GET TO IT.</i>

448
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:57,903
<i> DO WE HAVE
 SPEAKER CAPABILITY ?</i>

449
00:18:57,903 --> 00:19:00,972
IT'LL JUST TAKE A SECOND, SIR.

450
00:18:57,903 --> 00:19:00,972
MARSH, MS. REDFORD,
I NEED YOU TO LISTEN...

451
00:19:00,972 --> 00:19:03,007
TO THESE CONVERSATIONS
CAREFULLY.

452
00:19:03,007 --> 00:19:05,644
DECISIONS WE MAKE
MUST BE MADE INSTANTANEOUSLY.

453
00:19:05,644 --> 00:19:08,513
MARSH, TALK TO THE IBS FELLOW.
MAKE SURE HE'S NOT TAPING.

454
00:19:08,513 --> 00:19:11,283
THE PHONE IS READY.
THE SECRETARY OF DEFENSE.

455
00:19:08,513 --> 00:19:11,283
PUT YOUR CAMERA DOWN, PLEASE.

456
00:19:11,283 --> 00:19:16,388
OKAY.  DON, SUPPOSE YOU TELL ME
WHY I'M HEARING ABOUT THE START
OF WORLD WAR III ON THE TV.

457
00:19:16,388 --> 00:19:20,324
[ Secretary of Defense ]
THAT MAY BE OVERSTATING IT
A BIT, SIR.

458
00:19:20,325 --> 00:19:23,929
MR. SECRETARY, I MAY ONLY
BE HOLDING THIS OFFICE
FOR FOUR MONTHS,

459
00:19:23,929 --> 00:19:25,864
BUT THE PRESIDENT
SELECTED ME HIS SUCCESSOR...

460
00:19:25,864 --> 00:19:29,100
BECAUSE OF
MY UNILATERAL UNDERSTANDING
OF FOREIGN AFFAIRS.

461
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:31,535
HELL, I DEPUTY-CHAIRED
THE NATIONAL SECURITY COUNCIL.

462
00:19:31,536 --> 00:19:33,972
SO WHY DON'T WE FOREGO
THE PATRONIZING CRAP...

463
00:19:33,972 --> 00:19:37,075
AND HAVE YOU EXPLAIN
TO YOUR COMMANDER-IN-CHIEF...

464
00:19:37,075 --> 00:19:40,445
WHY HE'S HEARING
ABOUT THIS ON IBS.

465
00:19:40,445 --> 00:19:42,679
WE'RE GETTING
THE PIECES TOGETHER, SIR.

466
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:44,516
THE S.O.B.
OVERRAN OUR POSITION ?

467
00:19:44,516 --> 00:19:46,684
IT APPEARS TO BE
A COMPLETE ANNIHILATION.

468
00:19:46,684 --> 00:19:49,421
WE HAVE A REPORT THEY EXECUTED
THE FEW PRISONERS THEY TOOK.

469
00:19:49,421 --> 00:19:52,456
THE WOMEN TOO ?

470
00:19:49,421 --> 00:19:52,456
THERE WERE NURSES AND
ADMINISTRATIVE PERSONNEL THERE,

471
00:19:52,456 --> 00:19:54,293
SO, UH, YES,
WOMEN TOO.

472
00:19:54,293 --> 00:19:56,695
ONE OF THEM WAS
AN APACHE HELICOPTER PILOT.

473
00:19:56,695 --> 00:20:00,165
WOMEN ?  THAT'S IMPORTANT.
THAT GIVES US
HIGH MORAL GROUND.

474
00:20:00,165 --> 00:20:02,568
HOW COULD WE HAVE BEEN
TAKEN BY SURPRISE LIKE THIS ?

475
00:20:02,568 --> 00:20:05,837
WE SAW THE ACTIVITY,
BUT WE THOUGHT IT WAS
A MILITARY EXERCISE.

476
00:20:05,837 --> 00:20:11,209
GULF WAR PROVISIONS FORBID
ANY IRAQI MOVEMENT IN THIS AREA,
EXERCISE OR OTHERWISE.

477
00:20:11,209 --> 00:20:14,947
[ Secretary of Defense ]
IT'S NOT THE FIRST TIME HE'S
VIOLATED THE U.N. PROVISION.

478
00:20:14,947 --> 00:20:18,216
WE DIDN'T FEEL
IT WARRANTED TAKING YOU
FROM YOUR CAMPAIGN.

479
00:20:18,216 --> 00:20:22,454
FRANK, UH, COME IN.
GENERAL LANCASTER
JUST WALKED IN, SIR.

480
00:20:22,454 --> 00:20:24,723
IS IT JUST
THE TWO OF YOU ?

481
00:20:22,454 --> 00:20:24,723
YES, SIR.

482
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:26,558
GENTLEMEN,
I WANT TO REMIND YOU...

483
00:20:26,558 --> 00:20:29,695
THAT WE SHOULD
KEEP THE NATURE
OF THE CLASSIFIED CONTENT...

484
00:20:29,695 --> 00:20:32,030
THAT'S BEING
DISCUSSED HERE
TO A MINIMUM.

485
00:20:32,030 --> 00:20:34,299
<i> THE PRESIDENT IS NOT
 IN A SECURE LOCATION.</i>

486
00:20:34,299 --> 00:20:37,535
<i> WE WILL BE
 IN A FEW HOURS.</i>

487
00:20:34,299 --> 00:20:37,535
<i> [ Lancaster ]
 I'M AFRAID WE DON'T HAVE TIME.</i>

488
00:20:37,535 --> 00:20:39,571
FRANK, DOES HE HAVE IT ?

489
00:20:39,571 --> 00:20:42,939
WHAT ?  HE HAS WHAT ?
NUCLEAR WEAPONS ?

490
00:20:42,940 --> 00:20:45,977
NO, SIR,
BIOLOGICAL AND CHEMICAL.

491
00:20:45,977 --> 00:20:48,346
[ Secretary of Defense ]
WE'RE LOOKING
AT A COMPUTER SCREEN.

492
00:20:48,346 --> 00:20:51,482
THE IMAGERY APPEARS TO DISPLAY
LAUNCHING PADS FOR IRAQI...

493
00:20:51,482 --> 00:20:54,453
TACTICAL, CHEMICAL
AND BIOLOGICAL WEAPONS.

494
00:20:54,453 --> 00:20:56,454
[ Lancaster ]
THE SITE THAT WE HAVE THERE...

495
00:20:56,454 --> 00:20:59,390
CONTAINS EIGHT
CANVAS-COVERED
MISSILE TRAILERS...

496
00:20:59,391 --> 00:21:02,293
AND FOUR DEPLOYED
PROBABLE MISSILE LAUNCHERS.

497
00:21:02,293 --> 00:21:04,862
HOW FAR ADVANCED IS THIS ?

498
00:21:02,293 --> 00:21:04,862
I'VE NEVER SEEN...

499
00:21:04,863 --> 00:21:07,432
THIS KIND
OF INSTALLATION BEFORE.

500
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:09,434
THESE ARE
M.R.B.M.s.

501
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:09,434
OKAY.

502
00:21:09,434 --> 00:21:12,103
ARE THEY READY TO BE FIRED,
ANY OF THEM ?

503
00:21:12,103 --> 00:21:14,373
[ Secretary of Defense ]
THAT WOULD DEPEND
ON THEIR GROUND SUPPORT.

504
00:21:14,373 --> 00:21:16,307
I'M HESITANT TO SAY,
BUT CONSERVATIVELY,

505
00:21:16,307 --> 00:21:18,776
THE EARLIEST
THEY COULD LAUNCH
IS IN ONE HOUR, FORTY MINUTES.

506
00:21:18,776 --> 00:21:21,513
THEY LOOK POSITIONED
TO ATTACK TEL AVIV.

507
00:21:18,776 --> 00:21:21,513
TEL AVIV.

508
00:21:21,513 --> 00:21:23,415
<i> IN ISRAEL,
 SIR.</i>

509
00:21:21,513 --> 00:21:23,415
<i> THANK YOU.</i>

510
00:21:23,415 --> 00:21:25,684
AND GREECE
 AND TURKEY AS WELL.

511
00:21:25,684 --> 00:21:29,687
-<i> WHERE ARE THESE LAUNCH PADS ?
 - OUTSIDE RABAT, A FEW CLICKS
   FROM THE TURKISH BORDER.</i>

512
00:21:29,688 --> 00:21:32,490
THEY'RE MOBILE.
THAT EXPLAINS WHY
WE HAD NOT YET SEEN THEM.

513
00:21:32,490 --> 00:21:35,927
JESUS.  MARSH,
WHO'S RUNNING THE SHOW
OVER AT IBS ?

514
00:21:35,927 --> 00:21:37,928
CARL ISAACSON.

515
00:21:35,927 --> 00:21:37,928
ISAACSON.

516
00:21:37,929 --> 00:21:40,998
HOWARD, YOU WANT TO HOOK UP
THIS ISAACSON FELLOW
WITH MARSH ?

517
00:21:40,998 --> 00:21:43,768
THEN GET ME BEN-RAZZI.
I'M SURE HE'S ON TOP
OF THIS ALREADY.

518
00:21:43,768 --> 00:21:46,337
<i> MARSH, I'M GOING
 TO HAVE TO ADDRESS
 THE NATION.</i>

519
00:21:46,337 --> 00:21:49,675
- LET'S TALK TO THIS IBS GUY--
- NO, NO, NO.  NO, I DON'T THINK
  YOU SHOULD ADDRESS THE NATION.

520
00:21:49,675 --> 00:21:52,277
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

521
00:21:49,675 --> 00:21:52,277
JUST MAKE IT HAPPEN.

522
00:21:52,277 --> 00:21:55,480
BUT THE WRITERS
AREN'T EVEN HERE.

523
00:21:52,277 --> 00:21:55,480
PLEASE.

524
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:59,651
OKAY.  UH, HOWARD,
AS SOON AS YOU GOT
ISAACSON, LET ME KNOW.

525
00:21:59,651 --> 00:22:01,519
BRING HIM
RIGHT UP.

526
00:22:01,519 --> 00:22:04,422
GIVE ME WHAT OUR TROOP
MOBILIZATION STATUS IS.

527
00:22:04,422 --> 00:22:07,725
WE CAN BEGIN DEFCON 1
AND MOBILIZATION
OF 3,000...

528
00:22:07,725 --> 00:22:09,860
IN LESS THAN
AN HOUR.

529
00:22:09,860 --> 00:22:12,164
WE WOULD RELEASE
THE TACTICAL FIGHTER WING
AT LANGLEY...

530
00:22:12,164 --> 00:22:14,632
AND THEN
THE DIVISION READY BRIGADE
AT THE 82nd.

531
00:22:14,632 --> 00:22:16,835
AND THAT WOULD
PUT THEM IN IRAQ WHEN ?

532
00:22:16,835 --> 00:22:19,437
PARTIAL PROLIFERATION
IN TEN DAYS.

533
00:22:19,437 --> 00:22:22,439
THEN WE'D HAVE
TO SLASH OUR TROOP STRENGTH
IN THE KOREAS.

534
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:24,976
BUT I BELIEVE--
I'M SORRY, SIR.
MAY I INTERRUPT ?

535
00:22:24,976 --> 00:22:28,980
I BELIEVE PREMIER KIM
WHEN HE SAYS THAT
A DOWNSIZING OF OUR TROOPS...

536
00:22:28,980 --> 00:22:31,049
ON THE 38th PARALLEL
WILL PROPEL HIM...

537
00:22:31,049 --> 00:22:33,251
INTO A FLAT-OUT INVASION
OF NORTH KOREA.

538
00:22:33,251 --> 00:22:37,021
I'M NOT GONNA DROP A DOMINO
AND ALLOW CHINA TO WALK
INTO JAPAN, BOTTOM LINE.

539
00:22:37,021 --> 00:22:39,658
I'M CERTAINLY
NOT GONNA OFFER UP
ANOTHER TINY FORCE,

540
00:22:39,658 --> 00:22:42,493
NAKED AND VULNERABLE
TO HUSSEIN IN THE GULF,

541
00:22:42,493 --> 00:22:44,896
NOT LIKE THE 300
THAT JUST DIED.

542
00:22:44,896 --> 00:22:46,731
YEAH.

543
00:22:44,896 --> 00:22:46,731
RIGHT, SIR.

544
00:22:46,731 --> 00:22:49,667
ARE YOU TELLING ME
THAT WE HAVE NO MANPOWER
IN THE GULF AREA ?

545
00:22:49,667 --> 00:22:51,837
-<i> THERE IS ONE CARRIER.
  IT'S THE</i> U.S.S.--
- WAIT.  HOLD IT.

546
00:22:51,837 --> 00:22:53,972
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL US
THERE WAS A CARRIER ?

547
00:22:53,972 --> 00:22:57,142
WHAT DO YOU THINK THE POINT
OF THIS CONVERSATION IS ?

548
00:22:53,972 --> 00:22:57,142
SIR, I WAS JUST ABOUT TO--

549
00:22:57,142 --> 00:23:01,079
NOW YOU'RE TELLING US
THERE'S ONE CARRIER.

550
00:22:57,142 --> 00:23:01,079
THEU.S.S. POWELL.

551
00:23:01,079 --> 00:23:02,981
UH, HOLD ON, SIR.
HOLD ON, PLEASE.

552
00:23:01,079 --> 00:23:02,981
YES ?

553
00:23:02,981 --> 00:23:05,984
WE'RE JUST GETTING
THE PICTURES
FROM THE N.P.I.C.

554
00:23:05,984 --> 00:23:07,918
<i> [ Marsh ]
 WHAT'S THAT ?
 IS THAT OURS ?</i>

555
00:23:07,919 --> 00:23:11,990
IBS CORRESPONDENTS
HAVE CONFIRMED THAT THREE
IRAQI DIVISIONS--

556
00:23:11,990 --> 00:23:14,392
THE HAMMURABI,
THE MEDINA LUMINOUS...

557
00:23:14,392 --> 00:23:17,461
AND THE IN GOD WE TRUST--
ARE IN KUWAIT.

558
00:23:17,461 --> 00:23:19,898
THE KUWAITI MILITARY FORCE
OF A FEW THOUSAND TROOPS...

559
00:23:19,898 --> 00:23:22,867
MUST NOW CONTEND
WITH A HALF A MILLION
IRAQI TROOPS.

560
00:23:22,867 --> 00:23:25,503
UDEI'S NOT GONNA MAKE
THE SAME MISTAKES
HIS FATHER MADE.

561
00:23:25,503 --> 00:23:27,871
HE'S NOT GONNA WAIT FOR US
TO BUILD UP OUR STRENGTH.

562
00:23:25,503 --> 00:23:27,871
ALL RIGHT.

563
00:23:27,872 --> 00:23:31,409
THERE'S NO TOUGHER
MILITARY PROPOSITION
THAN REVERSING AN INVASION,

564
00:23:31,409 --> 00:23:33,311
BUT THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT WE'RE GOING TO DO.

565
00:23:33,311 --> 00:23:35,846
I'M GONNA HANG UP THE LINE.
I'LL BE BACK TO YOU
IN TEN MINUTES.

566
00:23:35,846 --> 00:23:38,550
WHEN I DO, I EXPECT TO BE ABLE
TO CONFERENCE CALL.  HOWARD ?

567
00:23:38,550 --> 00:23:41,119
CONFERENCE CALL MAKES
OUR LINE UNSECURE, SIR.

568
00:23:41,119 --> 00:23:43,420
HOW MANY SPEAKERPHONES
CAN WE SET UP, THEN ?

569
00:23:43,421 --> 00:23:46,224
WE HAVE FOUR SECURE
SATELLITE SPEAKERPHONES
LIKE THIS ONE.

570
00:23:46,224 --> 00:23:48,293
THEY'RE TRAINED ON
THE SIERRA SYSTEM.

571
00:23:48,293 --> 00:23:50,460
BUT WE'VE GOT SOME
CELL PHONES, DON'T WE ?

572
00:23:50,461 --> 00:23:52,864
NO, THOSE ARE UTTERLY IMPOSSIBLE
IN TERMS OF SECURITY.

573
00:23:52,864 --> 00:23:55,667
I THINK WHAT WE SHOULD DO
IS WE SHOULD STICK
WITH THE SATELLITES,

574
00:23:55,667 --> 00:23:57,903
AND I'LL PLACE THE CALLS
THROUGH MY Q-LINE.

575
00:23:57,903 --> 00:24:00,805
THERE ARE SEVERAL UNAUTHORIZED
PEOPLE HERE.  I DON'T THINK--

576
00:23:57,903 --> 00:24:00,805
THAT IS MY DECISION.

577
00:24:00,805 --> 00:24:04,342
I WANT CABINET MEMBERS
AND ANY ESSENTIAL MILITARY
PERSONNEL AT THE READY.

578
00:24:04,342 --> 00:24:06,944
<i> [ Marsh ]
 MAJOR CODDINGTON.</i>

579
00:24:04,342 --> 00:24:06,944
<i> YES, SIR.</i>

580
00:24:06,944 --> 00:24:08,747
TAKE A POSITION BY THE BOOTH,

581
00:24:08,747 --> 00:24:12,450
AND ACCESS ONLY
TO THE PRESIDENT, MYSELF
AND, UH, AND REDFORD.

582
00:24:12,450 --> 00:24:14,586
NO PROBLEM, SIR.

583
00:24:12,450 --> 00:24:14,586
ALL RIGHT.

584
00:24:14,586 --> 00:24:16,554
YOU GOT A MAP ?

585
00:24:14,586 --> 00:24:16,554
UH, I DON'T THINK--

586
00:24:16,554 --> 00:24:19,457
I CAN CHECK IN THE VAN.
YOU LOOKING FOR A MAP
OR A GLOBE ?

587
00:24:16,554 --> 00:24:19,457
A MAP.

588
00:24:19,457 --> 00:24:22,293
<i> HOWARD, WHAT ABOUT, UH--
 YOU GOT A LAPTOP ?</i>

589
00:24:22,293 --> 00:24:24,360
CAN YOU PULL UP AN ATLAS
ON THE INTERNET ?

590
00:24:24,361 --> 00:24:26,297
SIR, THE I-LINE MEMORY'S
NOT GOING TO ACCOMMODATE THAT.

591
00:24:26,297 --> 00:24:30,668
I THINK IF YOU GET RID
OF ONE OF THESE PHONES--

592
00:24:26,297 --> 00:24:30,668
NO, I NEED THE PHONE LINES.

593
00:24:30,668 --> 00:24:33,838
ARE YOU TELLING ME
ALL I HAVE AT MY DISPOSAL
TO BATTLE GLOBAL CRISIS...

594
00:24:33,838 --> 00:24:35,674
IS FOUR PHONES
IN A DINER ?

595
00:24:35,674 --> 00:24:37,976
FOUR SECURE
SATELLITE PHONES, SIR.

596
00:24:37,976 --> 00:24:39,944
SIR ?

597
00:24:37,976 --> 00:24:39,944
<i> [ Emerson ]
 YES.</i>

598
00:24:39,944 --> 00:24:41,846
SIR, WE HAVE A MAP
IN THE BACK.

599
00:24:41,846 --> 00:24:44,683
FINE.  THANK YOU.
COULD YOU GET IT, PLEASE,
AND SET IT UP OVER HERE ?

600
00:24:44,683 --> 00:24:47,218
SIR, I HAVE
MR. ISAACSON FOR YOU.

601
00:24:47,218 --> 00:24:49,621
HELLO.  MR. ISAACSON.

602
00:24:47,218 --> 00:24:49,621
HEY, HOW ARE YOU ?

603
00:24:49,621 --> 00:24:51,723
YEAH.  YEAH.
OH, WELL, HOLD ON.

604
00:24:51,723 --> 00:24:54,926
[ Places Handset
  On Cradle ]

605
00:24:51,723 --> 00:24:54,926
YEAH, THIS IS MARSHALL THOMPSON.

606
00:24:54,926 --> 00:24:59,231
MR. THOMPSON, HOW ARE YOU ?
YOU JUST GOT ME.  I WAS
HEADING OUT THE DOOR.

607
00:25:00,297 --> 00:25:02,567
UH, YOU'RE AWARE
OF OUR SITUATION ?

608
00:25:02,567 --> 00:25:05,003
YEAH, WELL, OF COURSE.
I'M HEADED TO THE STATION.

609
00:25:05,003 --> 00:25:08,106
YEAH, YEAH, WELL,
IT'S OBVIOUSLY VERY GRAVE.

610
00:25:08,106 --> 00:25:11,041
NOW, THE PRESIDENT NEEDS TO MAKE
AN ADDRESS TO THE NATION.

611
00:25:11,041 --> 00:25:13,144
OKAY, WELL,
THAT'S GREAT.  SURE.

612
00:25:13,144 --> 00:25:17,314
WE HAVE ONE OF YOUR GUYS HERE
DOING A SORT OF &quot;DAY IN
THE LIFE OF THE CAMPAIGN&quot; DEAL.

613
00:25:17,314 --> 00:25:19,617
YEAH, RIGHT.  NOAH BOYD.
HE'S ONE OF OUR TOP GUYS.

614
00:25:19,617 --> 00:25:22,620
YEAH, WELL, I NEVER
LIKED THE IDEA, BUT WE
COULD TURN THIS AROUND...

615
00:25:22,621 --> 00:25:24,756
AND MAKE THIS BENEFICIAL
TO ALL OF US, OKAY ?

616
00:25:24,756 --> 00:25:27,192
IN WHAT WAY ?

617
00:25:24,756 --> 00:25:27,192
NOW, IT'S
THE DARNDEST THING.

618
00:25:27,192 --> 00:25:31,029
SEE, WE'RE STUCK HERE.
WE'RE TRAPPED IN A DINER IN--
WHERE ARE WE ?

619
00:25:31,029 --> 00:25:33,598
[ Katie ]
MORTY'S ROADSIDE DINER.

620
00:25:31,029 --> 00:25:33,598
NO, NO, TOWN, TOWN.

621
00:25:33,598 --> 00:25:36,700
- AZTEC, COLORADO.
- YEAH, WE'RE IN
  AZTEC, COLORADO.

622
00:25:36,700 --> 00:25:38,903
A-Z-T-E--  WHAT ?

623
00:25:36,700 --> 00:25:38,903
<i> HOME OF THE
 SCREAMING BEAVERS.</i>

624
00:25:38,903 --> 00:25:41,472
HOME OF THE SCREAMING BEAVERS.

625
00:25:41,472 --> 00:25:45,043
A-Z-T-E-C,
AND, UH, WE WERE
OUT CAMPAIGNING,

626
00:25:45,043 --> 00:25:48,146
AND, YOU KNOW, UH,
THEN THE STORM
CAME OUT OF NOWHERE.

627
00:25:48,146 --> 00:25:51,581
THE CARAVAN WAS ON ITS WAY
BACK TO AIR FORCE--
ANYWAY, WE'RE IN A DINER.

628
00:25:51,582 --> 00:25:55,286
SO THE PRESIDENT
HAS TO MAKE AN ADDRESS
TO THE NATION A.S.A.P.

629
00:25:55,286 --> 00:25:58,456
WELL, NO PROBLEM.
CAN YOU GIVE ME TO NOAH ?

630
00:25:55,286 --> 00:25:58,456
UH, YEAH, HE'S RIGHT--

631
00:25:58,456 --> 00:26:00,524
- NOAH.
- YES, SIR, I'M HERE.

632
00:26:00,525 --> 00:26:02,894
HE'S RIGHT HERE.

633
00:26:00,525 --> 00:26:02,894
IS THIS POSSIBLE,
NOAH ?

634
00:26:02,894 --> 00:26:05,763
NOTHING'S EVER A PROBLEM, SIR.
WE CAN GO THROUGH
THE I-COM LINE.

635
00:26:05,763 --> 00:26:08,499
TAKE ME LESS THAN
A MINUTE TO BOOT IT UP.

636
00:26:08,499 --> 00:26:10,468
[ Isaacson ]
OKAY, THAT'S--
THAT'S THAT, THEN.

637
00:26:10,468 --> 00:26:13,605
NOAH'S GOT
YOU COVERED.

638
00:26:10,468 --> 00:26:13,605
ALL RIGHT.  UH--

639
00:26:13,605 --> 00:26:16,274
[ Clears Throat ]
NOW HERE'S THE DEAL.

640
00:26:16,274 --> 00:26:18,208
THIS SPEECH IS YOURS EXCLUSIVE.

641
00:26:18,209 --> 00:26:23,381
ALL RECORDING DEVICES
WILL GO ON AND OFF
ACCORDING TO OUR INSTRUCTIONS.

642
00:26:23,381 --> 00:26:25,616
OKAY, LET ME
TALK TO NOAH.

643
00:26:23,381 --> 00:26:25,616
[ Marsh ]  YEAH.

644
00:26:25,616 --> 00:26:28,152
YES, SIR ?

645
00:26:25,616 --> 00:26:28,152
[ Isaacson ]
GOT THAT NOAH ?

646
00:26:28,152 --> 00:26:30,454
LOUD AND CLEAR.

647
00:26:28,152 --> 00:26:30,454
GOOD.

648
00:26:30,454 --> 00:26:33,425
OKAY.  ALL RIGHT.

649
00:26:30,454 --> 00:26:33,425
I'LL GET WORD
TO HIGHLAND HILLS.

650
00:26:35,327 --> 00:26:38,296
NOW, LISTEN.  I DON'T WANT
ANY OF THIS<i> 60 MINUTES
 HIDDEN CAMERA BULLSHIT.</i>

651
00:26:38,296 --> 00:26:40,465
STRAIGHTFORWARD.
YOU GO OVER THERE.

652
00:26:40,465 --> 00:26:43,435
SIR, I HAVE PRIME MINISTER
BEN-RAZZI ON THE PHONE.

653
00:26:46,504 --> 00:26:49,040
MR. PRIME MINISTER.

654
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:52,476
YES, SIR, I'M FULLY
AWARE OF THE GRAVITY
OF THE SITUATION.

655
00:26:54,145 --> 00:26:58,383
YES, SIR, WELL,
SOON MY COUNTRY WILL BE
AT A STATE OF FULL READINESS.

656
00:27:00,718 --> 00:27:04,589
I UNDERSTAND.
WHAT ?  NO, SIR.

657
00:27:04,589 --> 00:27:06,390
SIR, I BEG OF YOU
TO RECALL THOSE PLANES,

658
00:27:06,391 --> 00:27:09,761
OR AT LEAST
KEEP THEM IN YOUR AIRSPACE
FOR THE NEXT TEN MINUTES.

659
00:27:09,761 --> 00:27:13,531
NO, NO, I SEE THIS
NO DIFFERENTLY
THAN BUSH DID IN '91.

660
00:27:13,531 --> 00:27:17,335
AN INCURSION ON YOUR PART
WILL ONLY FORM AN ALLIANCE
AMONG THE ARAB NATIONS.

661
00:27:19,236 --> 00:27:21,706
WELL, MR. PRIME--
MR. PRIME MINISTER,

662
00:27:21,706 --> 00:27:25,342
I'VE MADE ARRANGEMENTS
TO GO ON IBS LIVE...

663
00:27:25,343 --> 00:27:27,912
IN A COUPLE OF MINUTES HERE.

664
00:27:27,912 --> 00:27:30,214
GLOBALLY, YES.

665
00:27:30,214 --> 00:27:33,918
EXACTLY.  EXACTLY.

666
00:27:33,918 --> 00:27:37,522
THAT WOULD--
THAT'S ALL I'M ASKING.
THAT WOULD BE GREAT.

667
00:27:38,656 --> 00:27:40,524
YES, SIR.

668
00:27:40,525 --> 00:27:43,895
I DON'T THINK YOU'LL HAVE
ANY NEED TO TAKE AN OFFENSIVE
ACTION AT THAT POINT.

669
00:27:43,895 --> 00:27:46,898
ALL RIGHT.
THANK YOU, MR. PRIME MINISTER.

670
00:27:48,032 --> 00:27:49,900
OKAY.

671
00:27:48,032 --> 00:27:49,900
THE PRIME MINISTER
HAS AGREED...

672
00:27:49,901 --> 00:27:52,070
TO KEEP HIS AIR FORCE
IN ABEYANCE UNTIL AFTER
THE ADDRESS.

673
00:27:52,070 --> 00:27:56,006
LET'S KEEP AN OPEN,
SECURE LINE THERE.  OKAY.

674
00:27:56,007 --> 00:27:58,643
LET'S GET READY
FOR THE ADDRESS.

675
00:27:56,007 --> 00:27:58,643
OKAY.

676
00:27:58,643 --> 00:28:02,079
ALL RIGHT.
NO, OFF, OFF, OFF.

677
00:28:02,079 --> 00:28:03,982
WE'RE NOT READY YET.

678
00:28:05,950 --> 00:28:09,653
[ Marsh ]
FACTS, FIGURES, LOCATIONS
ARE NOT IMPORTANT RIGHT NOW.

679
00:28:09,653 --> 00:28:12,457
THE IMPORTANT THING
IS TO CONVEY A SENSE
OF DETERMINATION...

680
00:28:12,457 --> 00:28:14,525
ABOUT WHAT IT IS
WE'RE GONNA DO AS A COUNTRY.

681
00:28:14,525 --> 00:28:17,495
THAT'S WHAT THE AMERICAN PEOPLE
HAVE TO HEAR.  THAT'S WHAT
THIS SPEECH IS ABOUT.

682
00:28:17,495 --> 00:28:19,798
I CAN VERIFY
WHAT HAS TAKEN PLACE,
OBVIOUSLY.

683
00:28:19,798 --> 00:28:23,000
YES.

684
00:28:19,798 --> 00:28:23,000
AND THEN I NEED TO BE
VERY, VERY SPECIFIC.

685
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:26,270
YEAH.  IF YOU FIND YOURSELF
IN GENERAL WATERS,
BE VERY SPECIFIC ABOUT IT.

686
00:28:26,270 --> 00:28:28,105
EXCUSE ME, MR. PRESIDENT.

687
00:28:28,105 --> 00:28:31,176
AS YOUR NATIONAL
SECURITY ADVISOR,
I MUST INFORM YOU...

688
00:28:31,176 --> 00:28:35,513
THAT WHAT YOU'RE ABOUT TO DO
IS NOT IN YOUR BEST INTEREST
OR THAT OF THE COUNTRY.

689
00:28:35,513 --> 00:28:38,382
NOTED.  ON THE RECORD.
HOWEVER, HE IS GOING ON
IN A FEW MINUTES.

690
00:28:38,383 --> 00:28:41,352
<i> SO IS THERE ANYTHING
 THAT YOU CAN ADVISE
 THE PRESIDENT...</i>

691
00:28:41,352 --> 00:28:44,555
<i> THAT WOULD BE HELPFUL
 FOR WHAT HE IS ABOUT TO SAY
 TO THE AMERICAN PEOPLE ?</i>

692
00:28:44,555 --> 00:28:47,758
IF UDEI IS IN KUWAIT
ON HIS WAY TO SAUDI ARABIA,

693
00:28:47,758 --> 00:28:50,862
THAT MEANS
THAT HE HAS CLEARED OUT
ALL OF THE MINEFIELDS.

694
00:28:50,862 --> 00:28:55,099
WE ARE NOT TALKING
BRIGADES HERE.
WE ARE TALKING<i> ARMIES.</i>

695
00:28:55,099 --> 00:28:57,101
I APPRECIATE THAT
VERY MUCH--

696
00:28:55,099 --> 00:28:57,101
THE REPUBLICAN GUARD...

697
00:28:57,101 --> 00:29:00,672
IS OUT IN FULL FORCE,
AND THAT IS A TOTALLY
DIFFERENT MATTER HERE, SIR.

698
00:29:00,672 --> 00:29:02,773
THE DEBATE IS OVER.
I'M GOING ON THE AIR.

699
00:29:00,672 --> 00:29:02,773
NOAH ?

700
00:29:02,773 --> 00:29:05,443
YES.

701
00:29:02,773 --> 00:29:05,443
WE HAVE TO BRING THE MONITOR
OVER WHERE I CAN READ IT...

702
00:29:05,443 --> 00:29:07,311
AND THE PRESIDENT
CAN SEE IT.

703
00:29:07,311 --> 00:29:09,379
[ Noah ]
I'M JUST GRABBING
MY TRIPOD.  JUST A SEC.

704
00:29:09,380 --> 00:29:11,382
<i> I'LL WATCH THE MONITOR
 AND MAKE SURE THAT IBS--</i>

705
00:29:11,382 --> 00:29:14,051
<i> REMEMBER,
 IBS IS WAY AHEAD
 OF EVERYBODY ON THIS.</i>

706
00:29:14,051 --> 00:29:16,153
EVERYBODY KNOWS BASICALLY
WHAT'S GOING ON.

707
00:29:16,153 --> 00:29:19,257
I NEED TO GO ON
AND BE VERY SPECIFIC
ABOUT WHAT I'M DOING ABOUT IT.

708
00:29:19,257 --> 00:29:21,726
<i> YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
 WHO CAN DO THAT.</i>

709
00:29:19,257 --> 00:29:21,726
<i> LET'S DO THIS.</i>

710
00:29:21,726 --> 00:29:23,827
<i> [ Marsh ]
 WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
 HOLD IT, HOLD IT.</i>

711
00:29:23,827 --> 00:29:26,631
WE NEED A DIFFERENT CHAIR.
THIS CHAIR IS NOT ANY GOOD.

712
00:29:26,631 --> 00:29:29,867
IT'S THE ONLY CHAIR
WE GOT.

713
00:29:26,631 --> 00:29:29,867
THIS IS RIDICULOUS,
 THIS CHAIR.

714
00:29:29,867 --> 00:29:32,570
THERE ARE AT LEAST THREE
ARMORED DIVISIONS IN KUWAIT.

715
00:29:32,570 --> 00:29:35,339
OKAY, NOW, LISTEN.
IN THE RED ?

716
00:29:35,339 --> 00:29:37,609
BAD COLOR.
IT'S A DISTRACTION.
IF YOU COULD JUST--

717
00:29:37,609 --> 00:29:39,776
EVERYBODY, ACTUALLY,
JUST MOVE TO THAT SIDE.

718
00:29:39,777 --> 00:29:42,547
[ Irving ]
IRAQ STILL USES SOVIET MIGs
IN ITS AIR FORCE.

719
00:29:42,547 --> 00:29:45,549
I THINK YOU SHOULD WEAR
A BLAZER.

720
00:29:42,547 --> 00:29:45,549
OKAY.

721
00:29:45,549 --> 00:29:48,052
ALL RIGHT,
UH, COULD YOU
GET A BLAZER ?

722
00:29:48,052 --> 00:29:50,788
AT LEAST ONE MORE IRAQI DIVISION
HAS ENTERED THE FRAY--

723
00:29:50,788 --> 00:29:53,258
FORTY-FIVE SECONDS
BEFORE WE GET LIVE !

724
00:29:50,788 --> 00:29:53,258
DEX, DEX.

725
00:29:53,258 --> 00:29:56,360
NO TIME.

726
00:29:53,258 --> 00:29:56,360
ALL RIGHT, COME BACK.
WE NEED TO GO OVER YOUR SPEECH.

727
00:29:56,360 --> 00:29:59,796
[ Man ]
ONE THING IS CLEAR, AND THAT IS
THAT THIS IS A LARGE ARMY.

728
00:29:59,797 --> 00:30:04,335
EMERSON THE DIPLOMAT,
 EMERSON THE PEACEKEEPER,

729
00:30:04,335 --> 00:30:06,437
EMERSON
THE COOLHEADED.

730
00:30:06,437 --> 00:30:09,240
I HEAR YOU, MARSH.
IT'S GONNA BE GOOD.

731
00:30:09,240 --> 00:30:11,675
<i> [ Emerson ]
 IT'S GOING TO BE FINE.
 THANK YOU.</i>

732
00:30:11,675 --> 00:30:14,745
- WE'VE JUST RECEIVED WORD--
- BACK AGAINST THE WALL.
  PLEASE BE QUIET DURING THIS.

733
00:30:14,745 --> 00:30:17,681
<i> THE PRESIDENT WILL BE
 ADDRESSING THE NATION.</i>

734
00:30:14,745 --> 00:30:17,681
<i> THERE IS NO TIME DELAY.</i>

735
00:30:17,682 --> 00:30:19,783
WHEN GERALD GOES TO YOU,
START SPEAKING NATURALLY.

736
00:30:19,783 --> 00:30:22,386
RIGHT HERE.
I'LL BE WATCHING THAT.

737
00:30:22,386 --> 00:30:24,455
...FROM A DINER
IN AZTEC, COLORADO.

738
00:30:24,455 --> 00:30:27,925
NICE AND STILL.
WATCH FOR MY CUE.

739
00:30:24,455 --> 00:30:27,925
[ Irving ]  READY ?  VERY GOOD.

740
00:30:27,925 --> 00:30:31,595
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
THE PRESIDENT
OF THE UNITED STATES.

741
00:30:31,595 --> 00:30:34,532
HERE WE GO.

742
00:30:31,595 --> 00:30:34,532
MY FELLOW AMERICANS,

743
00:30:34,532 --> 00:30:38,870
AS THE WORLD NOW KNOWS,
THE LEADER OF IRAQ,
UDEI HUSSEIN,

744
00:30:38,870 --> 00:30:44,841
IN COMPLETE DEFIANCE
OF U.N. RESOLUTIONS
687, 773 AND 883,

745
00:30:44,842 --> 00:30:48,879
HAS INVADED
THE EMIRATE OF KUWAIT
AS HIS FATHER DID IN 1990.

746
00:30:48,879 --> 00:30:52,549
IN THE PROCESS,
HE HAS KILLED SEVERAL
HUNDRED AMERICAN TROOPS...

747
00:30:52,549 --> 00:30:54,985
SERVING AS
A PEACEKEEPING FORCE.

748
00:30:54,986 --> 00:30:58,623
OUR INTELLIGENCE
ALSO INDICATES THAT AT LEAST
EIGHT IRAQI DIVISIONS...

749
00:30:58,623 --> 00:31:02,227
ARE HOLDING KUWAIT
AND PROGRESSING TO SAUDI ARABIA.

750
00:31:03,661 --> 00:31:06,564
THIS IS NOT THE ACT
OF A WARRIOR NOR A LEADER...

751
00:31:06,564 --> 00:31:08,733
BUT THAT OF A BARBARIAN.

752
00:31:10,101 --> 00:31:13,304
WE MUST NOW ASSUME THAT
UDEI HUSSEIN'S OBJECTIVE...

753
00:31:13,304 --> 00:31:15,573
IS ONE OF A MANIFEST DESTINY.

754
00:31:16,674 --> 00:31:19,243
AT PRESENT,
NEARLY 80% OF OUR TROOPS...

755
00:31:19,243 --> 00:31:22,714
ARE ON THE SEA OF JAPAN
OR THE 38th PARALLEL.

756
00:31:23,781 --> 00:31:27,084
TO PUT IT
AS BLUNTLY AS POSSIBLE,

757
00:31:27,084 --> 00:31:29,720
THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA
DOES NOT HAVE THE CAPABILITY...

758
00:31:29,720 --> 00:31:34,125
OF DEALING
WITH THE IRAQI INVASION FORCE
WITH CONVENTIONAL EXPEDITION.

759
00:31:35,526 --> 00:31:38,062
THERE ARE DEFINING MOMENTS
IN THE HISTORY OF EVERY NATION,

760
00:31:38,062 --> 00:31:42,165
MOMENTS WHICH DELINEATE
OUR STRENGTHS AND OUR CHARACTER.

761
00:31:42,165 --> 00:31:47,671
OFTEN THESE MOMENTS REQUIRE
THAT A HARDER RIGHT BE MADE
OVER AN EASIER WRONG.

762
00:31:47,671 --> 00:31:52,810
IT IS WITH THAT IN MIND THAT
I NOW WISH TO SPEAK DIRECTLY
TO THE IRAQI PEOPLE.

763
00:31:52,810 --> 00:31:54,779
UNLESS YOUR LEADER,
UDEI HUSSEIN,

764
00:31:54,779 --> 00:31:59,283
IMMEDIATELY WITHDRAWS
FROM HIS POSITION IN KUWAIT,

765
00:31:59,283 --> 00:32:02,620
LEAVING ALL WEAPONS BEHIND
WHERE THEY ARE,

766
00:32:03,621 --> 00:32:05,623
AND TURNS HIMSELF IN
FOR ARREST...

767
00:32:05,623 --> 00:32:08,026
AT THE AMERICAN EMBASSY
IN KUWAIT,

768
00:32:09,060 --> 00:32:11,161
I WILL AUTHORIZE THE DROPPING...

769
00:32:11,161 --> 00:32:14,599
OF A MULTI-MEGATON
NUCLEAR DEVICE
ON THE CITY OF BAGHDAD.

770
00:32:15,833 --> 00:32:18,903
I'M NOW GIVING YOU,
THE CITIZENS OF BAGHDAD,

771
00:32:18,903 --> 00:32:21,773
ONE HOUR AND TWENTY MINUTES
TO LEAVE THE CITY,

772
00:32:21,773 --> 00:32:24,074
SAVE YOUR LIVES
AND THOSE OF YOUR CHILDREN.

773
00:32:25,809 --> 00:32:30,815
IT IS MY DEEPEST AND MOST
HEARTFELT WISH AND PRAYER...

774
00:32:30,815 --> 00:32:33,518
THAT UDEI HUSSEIN
ACCEPT HIS RESPONSIBILITY...

775
00:32:33,518 --> 00:32:39,156
AS THE SOVEREIGN OF A NATION
AND A RESPONSIBLE MEMBER
OF THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY.

776
00:32:39,156 --> 00:32:41,259
THAT IS IT FOR NOW.

777
00:32:41,259 --> 00:32:43,261
GOD SAVE US ALL.

778
00:32:43,261 --> 00:32:45,196
THANK YOU.

779
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:51,435
OKAY, LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
IF YOU ARE JUST JOINING US,

780
00:32:51,435 --> 00:32:54,870
THE PRESIDENT
OF THE UNITED STATES
HAS JUST GIVEN WHAT MAY BE...

781
00:32:54,871 --> 00:32:57,641
THE MOST DRAMATIC SPEECH EVER
GIVEN BY A SITTING PRESIDENT.

782
00:32:54,871 --> 00:32:57,641
[ Marsh ]  JESUS.

783
00:32:57,641 --> 00:33:00,077
WHAT ?  WHAT ?

784
00:33:00,077 --> 00:33:03,214
WELL, I MEAN,
THAT WASN'T EXACTLY
PEACEMAKING, WAS IT ?

785
00:33:04,748 --> 00:33:06,484
SUBJECTIVE, ISN'T IT ?

786
00:33:06,484 --> 00:33:09,419
ALL RIGHT, THANK YOU, EVERYBODY.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

787
00:33:09,420 --> 00:33:13,290
HE WOULD ORDER
THE DROPPING OF A NUCLEAR BOMB
ON BAGHDAD UNLESS:

788
00:33:13,290 --> 00:33:18,762
ONE, UDEI HUSSEIN WITHDRAWS
AND RETREATS FROM KUWAIT;
TWO--

789
00:33:18,762 --> 00:33:20,531
[ Lancaster ]
ACCORDING TO WEATHER INTEL,

790
00:33:20,531 --> 00:33:22,633
NAVIGATING AN AIRCRAFT
TO YOUR POSITION
IS IMPOSSIBLE.

791
00:33:22,633 --> 00:33:26,871
WE COULD RISK IT AND TRY
SENDING A HELICOPTER TO YOU.

792
00:33:22,633 --> 00:33:26,871
NO, NO, NO, NO.

793
00:33:26,871 --> 00:33:28,706
WE COULD RISK SENDING
A HELICOPTER HERE,

794
00:33:28,706 --> 00:33:32,610
BUT WE CANNOT RISK
PUTTING THE PRESIDENT
ON A HELICOPTER OUT OF HERE.

795
00:33:32,610 --> 00:33:35,780
[ Defense Secretary ]  AGREED.
NORAD HAS DISPATCHED A WINTER
A.P.C. TO YOUR POSITION.

796
00:33:35,780 --> 00:33:38,014
IT SHOULD BE THERE
IN ABOUT AN HOUR.

797
00:33:35,780 --> 00:33:38,014
ALL RIGHT.

798
00:33:38,015 --> 00:33:41,552
WHAT WILL MY ABILITY BE
TO COMMUNICATE
ONCE INSIDE THE A.P.C. ?

799
00:33:41,552 --> 00:33:45,423
THERE ARE SHORTWAVES
ON ALL THE A.P.C.s,
HOWEVER THE LINES ARE NONSECURE.

800
00:33:45,423 --> 00:33:48,525
IF THEY'RE NONSECURE,
FORGET IT.  BOTTOM LINE,
WE WORK FROM HERE.

801
00:33:48,525 --> 00:33:51,662
MR. PRESIDENT,
ADMIRAL MILLER HERE,
CENTRAL COMMAND.

802
00:33:51,662 --> 00:33:54,365
WITH YOUR PERMISSION,
I'D LIKE TO SPEAK TO YOU
OFF SPEAKER.

803
00:33:54,365 --> 00:33:56,801
ADMIRAL, HUSSEIN'S WEAPONS
GO HOT IN AN HOUR AND A HALF.

804
00:33:56,801 --> 00:33:58,802
I WILL NOT HOLD
YOUR COMMENTS
AGAINST YOU.

805
00:33:58,802 --> 00:34:02,973
OKAY.  SIR, I MUST OBJECT
TO YOUR THREAT ON IBS.

806
00:34:02,973 --> 00:34:05,810
HUSSEIN'S WEAPONS CAN BE
DEALT WITH CONVENTIONALLY.

807
00:34:05,810 --> 00:34:09,478
OUR HIGH-TECH WEAPONS CAN DO
ALL THAT THE NUKES CAN DO--

808
00:34:05,810 --> 00:34:09,478
NO, NO, NO.

809
00:34:09,478 --> 00:34:12,482
WE'VE BEEN DOWN
THAT ROAD BEFORE.

810
00:34:09,478 --> 00:34:12,482
THAT'S
A GOOD POINT, SIR.

811
00:34:12,483 --> 00:34:15,019
THAT'S NOT A GOOD POINT.  WE'VE
BEEN DOWN THAT ROAD BEFORE.

812
00:34:12,483 --> 00:34:15,019
LISTEN, PEOPLE !

813
00:34:15,018 --> 00:34:19,256
LET'S BE CLEAR.
IF WE ATTACK, WE ATTACK,
AND IT'S GONNA BE MAJOR.

814
00:34:19,257 --> 00:34:21,192
I'M NOT GONNA SEND OVER
A COUPLE OF TOMAHAWKS,

815
00:34:21,192 --> 00:34:23,661
AND GET ON THE PHONE AND SAY,
&quot;HOW DO YOU LIKE THEM APPLES ?&quot;

816
00:34:23,661 --> 00:34:26,496
IT'S NEVER WORKED BEFORE.
HUSSEIN'S LIKE HIS OLD MAN.
HE'S A SURVIVOR.

817
00:34:26,496 --> 00:34:31,802
AFTER EVERY CALAMITY, HE EMERGES
DUSTING OFF HIS UNIFORM ASKING,
&quot;IS THAT IT ?&quot;

818
00:34:31,802 --> 00:34:35,039
[ Lancaster ]
EVEN A LIMITED AIR ATTACK
IS AN EXTENSIVE AIR ATTACK.

819
00:34:35,039 --> 00:34:37,374
IT'S NOT 20 OR 50 SORTIES
BUT HUNDREDS.

820
00:34:37,373 --> 00:34:39,976
[ Miller ]
WHICH THE<i> U.S.S. POWELL
 CAN'T ACCOMMODATE.</i>

821
00:34:39,976 --> 00:34:44,781
RIGHT.  THEN WE'D HAVE
TO MOVE INTO THEIR PLANES,
AIRFIELDS, SAM SITES.

822
00:34:44,782 --> 00:34:48,986
[ Miller ]  GRANTED,
BUT EVEN THAT DOESN'T LEAVE US
WITH JUST THE NUCLEAR OPTION.

823
00:34:48,985 --> 00:34:53,123
OKAY, OKAY.  BEFORE WE
CARRY OUT THE &quot;SHOULD WE
OR SHOULDN'T WE&quot; DEBATE,

824
00:34:53,123 --> 00:34:55,192
LET'S ENSURE
WHAT WE IN FACT CAN DO.

825
00:34:55,192 --> 00:34:57,728
GENERAL RILEY,
WHAT DO WE HAVE ?

826
00:34:55,192 --> 00:34:57,728
WELL, MR. PRESIDENT,

827
00:34:57,728 --> 00:34:59,696
AT STRATCOM
UNDER START 2,

828
00:34:59,696 --> 00:35:03,066
OUR MISSILES ARE NOW SET
ON A TRAJECTORY THAT ENDS
IN THE ATLANTIC.

829
00:35:03,066 --> 00:35:05,535
WHAT BRILLIANT
COMMANDER-IN-CHIEF
CAME UP WITH THAT ONE ?

830
00:35:05,536 --> 00:35:08,171
HOW LONG TO RESET
THE TARGET ?

831
00:35:05,536 --> 00:35:08,171
OUR RECORD'S 20 MINUTES.

832
00:35:08,171 --> 00:35:10,607
IT USED TO BE SHORTER,
BUT WE DE-ALERTED
FIVE YEARS AGO.

833
00:35:10,607 --> 00:35:13,110
<i> [ Emerson ]
 WHAT DO WE HAVE
 IN OUR ARSENAL ?</i>

834
00:35:13,110 --> 00:35:15,146
[ Riley ]
SEVERAL TRIPLE WARHEAD
EXCALIBUR 3 NUCLEAR MISSILES.

835
00:35:15,146 --> 00:35:18,248
- WE COULD HIT OUR DESIGNATED
  TARGETS IN TWO HOURS.
- [ Emerson ]  TWO HOURS ?

836
00:35:18,248 --> 00:35:21,552
<i> NO, THAT'S UNACCEPTABLE.
 WE HAVE TO HIT IRAQ BEFORE
 THEIR WEAPONS CAN GO HOT.</i>

837
00:35:21,552 --> 00:35:24,121
HOW THE UNITED STATES
WOULD LAUNCH A NUCLEAR ATTACK,

838
00:35:24,121 --> 00:35:28,559
PARTICULARLY WHEN IT MUST BE
INITIATED AND COMPLETED IN LESS
THAN AN HOUR AND A HALF...

839
00:35:28,559 --> 00:35:30,527
IS VERY LIMITING.

840
00:35:30,527 --> 00:35:32,362
WE DO HAVE FILE FOOTAGE HERE.

841
00:35:32,362 --> 00:35:36,767
THE<i> U.S.S. POWELL</i> IS
OUR ONE AND ONLY WARSHIP
IN THE GULF REGION.

842
00:35:36,767 --> 00:35:41,504
THE<i> POWELL</i> IS ONE
OF ONLY TWO SURFACE SHIPS
TO CARRY NUCLEAR WEAPONS...

843
00:35:41,505 --> 00:35:44,775
SINCE PRESIDENT BUSH'S
NUCLEAR BAN INSTITUTED IN 1992.

844
00:35:44,775 --> 00:35:48,546
[ Emerson ]
OKAY, WHAT WEAPONS
DO WE HAVE ON THEPOWELL<i> ?</i>

845
00:35:48,546 --> 00:35:51,515
[ Lancaster ]
THE FASTEST DEPLOYMENT
WOULD BE BY TOMAHAWK.

846
00:35:51,515 --> 00:35:54,518
DETONATION
IN 40 MINUTES.

847
00:35:51,515 --> 00:35:54,518
OKAY, BUT IF WE DO THAT,

848
00:35:54,518 --> 00:35:57,454
WE HAVE TO GIVE HUSSEIN
ENOUGH TIME TO COMPLY.

849
00:35:57,454 --> 00:35:59,489
WE COULD LAUNCH TOMAHAWKS
45 MINUTES FROM NOW.

850
00:35:59,489 --> 00:36:02,626
HE WOULD HAVE THAT TIME
PLUS AN ADDITIONAL 40
TO COMPLY, CORRECT ?

851
00:36:02,626 --> 00:36:06,898
[ Miller ]  NOT REALLY.
ONCE THAT MISSILE'S
ON ITS WAY, IT'S ON ITS WAY.

852
00:36:06,898 --> 00:36:09,867
THERE MUST BE SOME WAY
TO DIVERT IT, RIGHT ?

853
00:36:10,934 --> 00:36:12,603
[ Lancaster ]
WE CAN DO TWO THINGS...

854
00:36:12,603 --> 00:36:14,905
IF HUSSEIN COMPLIES
WHILE THE MISSILE
IS IN FLIGHT.

855
00:36:14,905 --> 00:36:18,542
FIRSTLY, WE CAN DETONATE.

856
00:36:14,905 --> 00:36:18,542
THEN WE'D HAVE NUCLEAR RAIN
ALL OVER THE DETONATION AREA.

857
00:36:18,542 --> 00:36:21,310
POSSIBLY
A FRIENDLY ONE.

858
00:36:18,542 --> 00:36:21,310
EXACTLY, MA'AM.

859
00:36:21,311 --> 00:36:23,414
WE CAN ALSO
DEACTIVATE THE BOMB.

860
00:36:23,414 --> 00:36:25,849
THE PROBLEM IS THAT, THEN,
WHERE THE BOMB LANDS,
IT LANDS.

861
00:36:25,849 --> 00:36:28,619
AND THAT'S LIKE
GIVING HUSSEIN
A FREE NUCLEAR WEAPON.

862
00:36:28,619 --> 00:36:32,355
[ Lancaster ]  SIR,
I'D SAY OUR ONLY OPTION IS TO
ACTUALLY DROP A BOMB ON BAGHDAD.

863
00:36:32,355 --> 00:36:34,358
WE COULD USE OUR B-2s
BASED IN SAUDI.

864
00:36:34,358 --> 00:36:37,360
HOW LONG TO LOAD HER
AND PUT HER UP IN THE AIR ?

865
00:36:34,358 --> 00:36:37,360
ON YOUR ORDERS, SIR.

866
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:40,497
THE GOOD NEWS IS
THE B-2 CAN BE RECALLED
AT THE LAST SECOND IF NECESSARY.

867
00:36:40,497 --> 00:36:42,732
WE CAN STRIKE
WITHIN AN HOUR.

868
00:36:40,497 --> 00:36:42,732
THIS IS PROBLEMATIC.

869
00:36:42,733 --> 00:36:47,270
THE B-2s WE'D HAVE TO FLY
OVER SAUDI TERRITORY.
WE'D HAVE TO GET PERMISSION.

870
00:36:47,270 --> 00:36:49,740
THIS GUY IS INVADING
THEIR OIL FIELDS.

871
00:36:49,740 --> 00:36:52,975
OF COURSE WE'RE GONNA
GET PERMISSION.

872
00:36:49,740 --> 00:36:52,975
THERE IS NO &quot;OF COURSE.&quot;

873
00:36:52,976 --> 00:36:56,280
I KNOW THESE GUYS.

874
00:36:52,976 --> 00:36:56,280
SHARING A LITTLE<i> BABA GHANNOUJ
 AT A STATE DINNER...</i>

875
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:58,348
DOES NOT
MAKE YOU KNOW THEM.

876
00:36:58,348 --> 00:37:00,884
OKAY.  ALL RIGHT.
WE'RE GONNA PUT
THE B-2 UP.

877
00:37:00,884 --> 00:37:02,786
WE DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR PROTOCOL.

878
00:37:02,786 --> 00:37:05,556
SIR, IT IS NOT
A MATTER OF PROTOCOL.

879
00:37:05,556 --> 00:37:08,392
IT'S INTERNATIONAL LAW.

880
00:37:05,556 --> 00:37:08,392
UNDERSTOOD.

881
00:37:08,392 --> 00:37:12,428
CONSIDER IT AN ACT
OF CIVIL DISOBEDIENCE.

882
00:37:12,429 --> 00:37:17,535
GET ME SECRETARY OF STATE
AND, UH, GIVE ME
A FEW MINUTES, FOLKS.

883
00:37:28,245 --> 00:37:31,848
WHAT ARE YOU DOING ?
USE SOME COMMON SENSE.
COME ON.

884
00:37:31,848 --> 00:37:34,719
MM-HMM.
SPECIALTY OF THE HOUSE.

885
00:37:34,719 --> 00:37:37,221
OH, WOW.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

886
00:37:37,221 --> 00:37:40,124
BITCH OF A SITUATION
YOU'VE GOT ON YOUR HANDS.

887
00:37:40,124 --> 00:37:42,560
YES.  YES, IT IS.

888
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:46,998
- IF I WERE YOU--
- EXCUSE ME.  MAY WE HAVE
  A WORD HERE, PLEASE ?

889
00:37:51,535 --> 00:37:54,203
I'LL GET THAT.

890
00:37:51,535 --> 00:37:54,203
OKAY.  WOULD YOU
LIKE SOMETHING ?

891
00:37:54,204 --> 00:37:56,907
NO, I'M FINE.  THANKS.

892
00:37:56,907 --> 00:37:59,410
MR. PRESIDENT,
I WAS THINKING--

893
00:37:56,907 --> 00:37:59,410
GAYLE.

894
00:37:59,410 --> 00:38:02,078
WHAT CAN YOU
TELL ME ABOUT
ADMIRAL MILLER ?

895
00:38:02,079 --> 00:38:04,447
MILLER ?

896
00:38:02,079 --> 00:38:04,447
YES.

897
00:38:04,447 --> 00:38:07,184
DO YOU
KNOW HIM ?

898
00:38:07,184 --> 00:38:11,855
HE WAS ONE OF THE PRESIDENT'S
NOMINEES FOR CHAIR OF THE J.C.S.
TWO YEARS AGO.

899
00:38:11,855 --> 00:38:13,790
HE LOST OUT TO LANCASTER.

900
00:38:13,790 --> 00:38:16,793
HE'S BEEN RUNNING
CENTRAL COMMAND EVER SINCE THEN.

901
00:38:16,793 --> 00:38:20,397
SOUTHWEST ASIA, THE MIDDLE EAST,
THOSE ARE HIS TERRITORIES,

902
00:38:20,397 --> 00:38:22,833
BUT HE'S BASED IN McDILL,
IN FLORIDA.

903
00:38:22,833 --> 00:38:25,603
THE ARAB COUNTRIES
DON'T WANT US
IN THE GULF AREA.

904
00:38:25,603 --> 00:38:28,105
MY GUESS IS
HE'S PROBABLY FEELING
LIKE A PAPER TIGER.

905
00:38:28,105 --> 00:38:29,907
YEAH, I THINK SO.

906
00:38:29,907 --> 00:38:34,411
THAT CERTAINLY EXPLAINS
THE GIANT CHIP ON HIS SHOULDER.

907
00:38:34,411 --> 00:38:36,547
IT'S A CHIP YOU NEED
RIGHT NOW, SIR.

908
00:38:36,547 --> 00:38:40,016
MADAM CHAIRMAN, WE JUST MIGHT
HAVE TO DROP THAT WEAPON.

909
00:38:40,016 --> 00:38:42,853
<i> IF WE DO--</i>

910
00:38:42,853 --> 00:38:44,788
<i> [ Sighing ]</i>

911
00:38:44,788 --> 00:38:49,626
YOU KNOW, TRUMAN DEBATED
AGONIZINGLY BEFORE HIROSHIMA.

912
00:38:49,626 --> 00:38:52,229
NOT SO MUCH
ABOUT DROPPING THE BOMB...

913
00:38:52,229 --> 00:38:55,298
BUT WHETHER OR NOT TO FOREWARN
THE JAPANESE PEOPLE.

914
00:38:55,298 --> 00:38:57,100
<i> WE'D HAVE
 WON THE WAR
 EITHER WAY,</i>

915
00:38:57,101 --> 00:39:01,305
<i> BUT HE WOULD HAVE
 SLEPT BETTER
 THE REST OF HIS LIFE.</i>

916
00:39:01,305 --> 00:39:05,375
I'M DETERMINED TO SPARE
AS MANY LIVES AS I CAN,

917
00:39:05,375 --> 00:39:08,379
AND I JUST, FOR THE LIFE OF ME,
CAN'T IMAGINE...

918
00:39:08,379 --> 00:39:12,316
HUSSEIN IS GONNA LET
THE CITY OF BAGHDAD DIE.

919
00:39:13,484 --> 00:39:15,652
<i> OUR STRATEGY IS
 TO ROLL THE DICE...</i>

920
00:39:15,652 --> 00:39:17,621
<i> THAT HE'LL COMPLY.</i>

921
00:39:20,056 --> 00:39:23,627
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT
TO YOUR VEGAS METAPHOR, SIR,

922
00:39:23,627 --> 00:39:26,196
NUCLEAR WARFARE
IS NOT ABOUT GAMBLING.

923
00:39:26,196 --> 00:39:28,665
IT'S ABOUT CERTAINTY.

924
00:39:28,665 --> 00:39:30,701
STRATEGIC CERTAINTY.

925
00:39:30,701 --> 00:39:32,770
MORAL CERTAINTY.

926
00:39:34,071 --> 00:39:36,207
<i> SECRETARY CLIFT
 IS ON THE PHONE.</i>

927
00:39:37,241 --> 00:39:40,478
DO I SEEM UNCERTAIN
TO YOU, GAYLE ?

928
00:39:44,648 --> 00:39:47,050
HUSSEIN, FOR EXAMPLE,
COULD WITHHOLD THE OIL FROM US,

929
00:39:47,050 --> 00:39:48,952
OR HE COULD FLOOD
THE WORLD MARKET.

930
00:39:48,952 --> 00:39:53,423
IN ANY CASE, HUSSEIN WILL HAVE
THE LEVERAGE TO MANIPULATE
OIL PRICES AT WILL,

931
00:39:53,423 --> 00:39:55,591
AND YOU CAN ASSUME THAT--
WELL, DON'T FORGET, GERALD,

932
00:39:55,592 --> 00:39:59,362
IN 1990, THE ONLY PEOPLE
SMILING WERE THE BOYS
AT EXXON AND SHELL,

933
00:39:59,362 --> 00:40:02,132
WHO SAW GAS PRICES
AND STOCKS--

934
00:39:59,362 --> 00:40:02,132
DEBRA, WHERE ARE YOU NOW ?

935
00:40:02,132 --> 00:40:06,036
<i> I'M ON MY WAY TO STATE.</i>

936
00:40:02,132 --> 00:40:06,036
<i> UH-HUH, AND WHAT
 ARE YOU SENSING ?</i>

937
00:40:06,036 --> 00:40:07,804
<i> WELL, I'M NOT
 SENSING SUPPORT.</i>

938
00:40:07,804 --> 00:40:10,608
<i> JUST ABOUT EVERYBODY
 IS DEMANDING AN AUDIENCE,</i>

939
00:40:10,608 --> 00:40:12,910
<i> AND ANDREA IN GREECE
 IS GOING TO DEFCON 1.</i>

940
00:40:12,910 --> 00:40:17,080
DEFCON 1 HAS GOT TO BE
THE LIMIT.  IT CANNOT ESCALATE
ONE INCH BEYOND THAT.

941
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:19,683
UNDERSTOOD.

942
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:19,683
OKAY, I'M GONNA, UH,

943
00:40:19,683 --> 00:40:23,353
ISSUE AN EXECUTIVE ORDER
FREEZING ALL KUWAITI ASSETS.

944
00:40:23,353 --> 00:40:26,023
MARSH, WE NEED TO GET ON
WITH TREASURY.

945
00:40:23,353 --> 00:40:26,023
YEAH.

946
00:40:26,023 --> 00:40:28,525
OR IS IT THE A.G. ?

947
00:40:26,023 --> 00:40:28,525
NO, I THINK
IT'S TREASURY.

948
00:40:28,525 --> 00:40:30,594
YEAH.  OKAY.
ALL RIGHT.

949
00:40:28,525 --> 00:40:30,594
IT'S TREASURY.

950
00:40:30,594 --> 00:40:33,664
THE OIL LOBBY
IS GONNA GO APE-SHIT.

951
00:40:30,594 --> 00:40:33,664
YEAH, I KNOW,

952
00:40:33,664 --> 00:40:36,667
BUT GET ON WITH NICHOLS
ANYWAYS AND GET THAT
ROLLING ON THE STAT.

953
00:40:36,667 --> 00:40:39,269
I'M SURE HE CAN WORK OFF
MY VERBAL DIRECTIVE FOR NOW.

954
00:40:39,269 --> 00:40:42,772
DEBRA, YOU NEED TO GET ON
WITH ANY OTHER FOREIGN NATION
THAT'LL DO THE SAME.

955
00:40:42,773 --> 00:40:45,608
WE NEED TO FREEZE THOSE ASSETS
BEFORE UDEI CAN GET TO THEM.

956
00:40:45,608 --> 00:40:47,944
GOT IT.

957
00:40:45,608 --> 00:40:47,944
OKAY,
AND I NEED GESTAING.

958
00:40:47,944 --> 00:40:52,783
MY GUESS IS THAT HE'LL FOLLOW
THE FRENCH PATTERN OF DENYING US
USE OF THEIR AIRSPACE.

959
00:40:52,783 --> 00:40:55,219
GIVE ME SOME TIME.
I THINK I CAN MAKE
HIS SQUARES.

960
00:40:55,219 --> 00:40:58,455
NO, FORGET THAT, OKAY ?
WHAT I NEED IS TO SPEAK
WITH GESTAING.

961
00:40:58,455 --> 00:41:00,290
VERY WELL.
AS YOU WILL.

962
00:41:00,290 --> 00:41:04,094
WHAT HAS BEEN MUCH LOUDER--
THIS IS COMING FROM
THE CONGRESSIONAL SIDE--

963
00:41:04,094 --> 00:41:06,163
IS WHAT SEVERAL MEMBERS
OF THE WHITE HOUSE--

964
00:41:06,163 --> 00:41:07,997
EXCUSE ME,
SEVERAL MEMBERS
OF THE HOUSE--

965
00:41:07,997 --> 00:41:11,535
ARE CALLING
A DELIBERATE VIOLATION
OF THE WAR POWERS ACT.

966
00:41:11,535 --> 00:41:13,636
WELL, UPDATE US
ON THAT.

967
00:41:13,637 --> 00:41:16,106
SIR, IT'S THE OVAL OFFICE,
LINE TWO, MR. OMARI.

968
00:41:17,107 --> 00:41:19,276
NO, NO, NO, NO,
 NO, NO, NO.

969
00:41:19,276 --> 00:41:21,678
MR. PRESIDENT,
THIS IS INAPPROPRIATE.

970
00:41:21,679 --> 00:41:24,514
YOU SHOULD NOT NEGOTIATE
WITH AN EMISSARY
FROM ANOTHER HEAD OF STATE.

971
00:41:24,514 --> 00:41:26,717
YOU SHOULD LEAVE THAT
TO GAYLE OR MYSELF.

972
00:41:24,514 --> 00:41:26,717
ABSOLUTELY.

973
00:41:26,717 --> 00:41:29,419
NORMALLY, YES.
DULY NOTED, BUT I
NEED TO DO THIS.

974
00:41:29,419 --> 00:41:31,721
- ON THE RECORD.
- RECORD.

975
00:41:32,890 --> 00:41:34,825
[ Beeping ]

976
00:41:32,890 --> 00:41:34,825
MR. OMARI ?

977
00:41:34,825 --> 00:41:38,028
IT'S ALICE, SIR.  I HAVE
MR. OMARI.  HE'S WITH
A TRANSLATOR.  GO AHEAD.

978
00:41:38,028 --> 00:41:41,165
MR. OMARI,
THIS IS THE PRESIDENT.

979
00:41:38,028 --> 00:41:41,165
[ Speaking Arabic ]

980
00:41:41,165 --> 00:41:45,335
[ Translator ]  I CALL YOU
ON A MATTER OF GRAVE CONCERN
TO MY GOVERNMENT, MR. EMERSON.

981
00:41:45,335 --> 00:41:47,471
YES, THIS IS VERY GRAVE.

982
00:41:47,471 --> 00:41:50,740
YOUR ANNOUNCEMENT HAS CREATED
HAVOC IN OUR STREETS.

983
00:41:50,740 --> 00:41:54,645
OUR HOSPITALS ARE FLOODED
WITH YOUNG CHILDREN,
THE VICTIMS OF STAMPEDES.

984
00:41:54,645 --> 00:41:57,247
I REQUEST OF YOU
A TAKING BACK OF YOUR COMMENT.

985
00:41:57,247 --> 00:41:59,816
MR. THOMPSON, SIR--

986
00:41:57,247 --> 00:41:59,816
<i> [ Emerson ]  GIVE US
 ONE SECOND, PLEASE.</i>

987
00:41:59,816 --> 00:42:02,185
WHAT IS IT ?

988
00:42:02,185 --> 00:42:04,054
FORGIVE ME,
MR. PRESIDENT,
BUT, UH,

989
00:42:04,054 --> 00:42:06,022
THIS MAN ISN'T TRANSLATING
CORRECTLY FOR YOU, SIR.

990
00:42:06,022 --> 00:42:08,325
WHAT DO YOU MEAN ?

991
00:42:06,022 --> 00:42:08,325
WELL, IT'S A LOT
OF THINGS.

992
00:42:08,325 --> 00:42:12,428
THEY'RE SMALL THINGS,
BUT THEY COULD ADD UP
TO SOMETHING BIG.

993
00:42:08,325 --> 00:42:12,428
LIKE ?

994
00:42:12,429 --> 00:42:14,899
HE SAID,
&quot;I REQUEST OF YOU,&quot;

995
00:42:14,899 --> 00:42:18,602
WHEN WHAT I HEARD
THIS OMARI REALLY SAY IS,
&quot;I DEMAND OF YOU.&quot;

996
00:42:18,602 --> 00:42:21,904
HE'S GOT A TONE
IN HIS VOICE, SIR.

997
00:42:18,602 --> 00:42:21,904
SO YOU SPEAK ARABIC ?

998
00:42:21,905 --> 00:42:23,908
YES, SIR.
I'M U.S. ARMY, RETIRED, M.I.

999
00:42:23,908 --> 00:42:26,543
- I WAS A DECRYPTOR
  IN DESERT STORM, SIR.
- IS THAT RIGHT ?

1000
00:42:26,543 --> 00:42:28,645
YES, SIR.
 YES, IT IS.

1001
00:42:26,543 --> 00:42:28,645
ALL RIGHT.

1002
00:42:28,645 --> 00:42:31,014
WELL, THEN,
WELCOME ABOARD.
YOU'RE OUR TRANSLATOR.

1003
00:42:31,014 --> 00:42:34,885
WHAT'S YOUR NAME ?

1004
00:42:31,014 --> 00:42:34,885
I'M SPECIAL AGENT DEXTER, SIR.

1005
00:42:34,885 --> 00:42:36,987
I'M IN CHARGE
OF YOUR DOMESTIC
TRAVELING DETAIL.

1006
00:42:34,885 --> 00:42:36,987
SHIT !

1007
00:42:36,987 --> 00:42:39,189
I SHOULD KNOW THAT.
I'M SORRY.
PLEASE, SIT DOWN.

1008
00:42:39,189 --> 00:42:43,125
EXCUSE ME, SPECIAL AGENT.
I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW, SIR,
THAT THIS IS NOT PRUDENT.

1009
00:42:43,126 --> 00:42:45,728
THERE'S A SPECIAL TRAINING
THAT GOES ALONG
WITH THIS LINE OF WORK.

1010
00:42:45,728 --> 00:42:47,998
NATURALLY.  THERE ISN'T
TIME FOR THAT.

1011
00:42:45,728 --> 00:42:47,998
I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW THAT.

1012
00:42:47,998 --> 00:42:50,000
I APPRECIATE IT.
OKAY.

1013
00:42:47,998 --> 00:42:50,000
YOU'RE WELCOME.

1014
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:53,403
UH, LISTEN CAREFULLY,
SPEAK CAREFULLY,
OBVIOUSLY,

1015
00:42:53,403 --> 00:42:55,372
AND, UH,
DO YOUR BEST.

1016
00:42:55,372 --> 00:42:57,207
I WILL, SIR.

1017
00:42:55,372 --> 00:42:57,207
OKAY.

1018
00:42:58,342 --> 00:43:00,410
[ Marsh ]
OKAY, AND ALL SET ?

1019
00:42:58,342 --> 00:43:00,410
READY.

1020
00:43:00,410 --> 00:43:02,546
